[Crim. No. 1117. Third Appellate District. April 7, 1930.] THE PEOPLE, Respondent, v. EVANS WHITE FINCH, Appellant.

*106Evans White Finch, in pro. per., for Appellant.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and J. Charles Jones, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

The defendant was convicted in the Superior Court of Sacramento County of a.felony, to wit: Robbery of the first degree.

The transcript on appeal was filed in this court February 20, 1930. No brief has been filed in behalf of appellant. The cause was regularly placed on the calendar for oral argument on April 7, 1930. No appearance was made for appellant at the time the case was called for hearing. Pursuant to the provisions of section 1253 of the Penal Code, the judgment and the order are affirmed.
